                    <span>This is by far the worst SQL Svr book I've read. Many, many important details are glossed over without so much as a word. For example, where is the discussion of the importance of constraints in sound DB design for performance? You know that the query optimizer uses them, right? Where is the discussion of index fragmentation? How about statistic histograms? This book was written by someone who is at best a SQL perf amateur. Don't waste your money.</span>
                  
